# React Naming Conventions (REQUIRED)

Standardized naming conventions for functions, handlers, props, and callbacks in React components. Follow these rules to maintain consistency and readability throughout the codebase.

---

## 1. Handler Functions

### 1.1. Logic/Data Handlers - Format: `handle` + `Action` + `DataModel`

For functions that handle logic such as setting state, updating data, array operations, etc., always use the format:

```
handle + Action + DataModel
```

**Common actions**: `Update`, `Add`, `Remove`, `Reset`, `Back`, `Submit`, `Filter`, `Sort`, `Search`

**GOOD Examples**:

```tsx
// Data updates
const handleUpdateActiveCard = async (body: UpdateCardBodyType) => { ... }
const handleUpdateCardTitle = (title: string) => { ... }
const handleUpdateCardDescription = (description: string) => { ... }
const handleUpdateCardCoverPhoto = (coverPhoto: string) => { ... }
const handleUpdateCardDueDateAndStatus = (dueDate: Date | null, isCompleted: boolean | null) => { ... }
const handleUpdateCardMembers = (user: UserType) => { ... }

// Add/Remove items
const handleAddListItem = (item: ItemType) => { ... }
const handleRemoveListItem = (itemId: string) => { ... }

// Reset state
const handleResetFormData = () => { ... }
const handleCardDescriptionReset = () => { ... }

// Navigation logic
const handleBackToCardCoverPhoto = () => { ... }
```

### 1.2. UI Event Handlers - Format: `handle` + `DataModel` + `Action`

When `action` is one of the following: **click**, **change**, **open**, **close**, **toggle**, **select**, use the format:

```
handle + DataModel + Action
```

**GOOD Examples**:

```tsx
// Click events
const handleDatesMenuClick = (event: React.MouseEvent<HTMLButtonElement>) => { ... }
const handleSuggestionClick = (search: string) => { ... }

// Toggle events
const handleGroupActionsPopoverToggle = (event: React.MouseEvent<HTMLDivElement>) => { ... }
const handleCardCoverPopoverToggle = (event: React.MouseEvent<HTMLButtonElement>) => { ... }
const handleRemoveActiveCardPopoverToggle = (event: React.MouseEvent<HTMLButtonElement>) => { ... }
const handleCardCompletionStatusToggle = (event: React.ChangeEvent<HTMLInputElement>) => { ... }

// Open/Close events
const handleActiveCardModalClose = () => { ... }
const handleDatesMenuClose = () => { ... }
const handleCardCoverPopoverClose = () => { ... }
const handleRemoveActiveCardPopoverClose = () => { ... }
const handleDeleteBoardPopoverClose = () => { ... }
const handleClosedBoardsOpen = () => { ... }

// Change events
const handleWorkspaceChange = (event: SelectChangeEvent) => { ... }
const handleInputChange = (event: React.ChangeEvent<HTMLInputElement>) => { ... }

// Select events
const handleMemberSelect = (memberId: string) => { ... }
```

**BAD Examples** (non-compliant):

```tsx
// ❌ BAD: Action comes before DataModel for UI events
const handleCloseActiveCardModal = () => { ... }
const handleToggleGroupActionsPopover = () => { ... }
const handleOpenClosedBoards = () => { ... }

// ✅ GOOD:
const handleActiveCardModalClose = () => { ... }
const handleGroupActionsPopoverToggle = () => { ... }
const handleClosedBoardsOpen = () => { ... }
```

